<h1>Affix</h1>

<p>The content of an Affix widget will stay visible in the viewport when it's target element is also visible. By default, Affix will target the parent element.</p>

<p>The nav to the left is an example.</p>

<style>
    .affix-example.affix {
        top: 100px;
    }
    .affix-example.affix-bottom {
        position: absolute;
        top: auto;
        bottom: 14px;
    }
</style>

<h2>Stand alone widget</h2>
<p>Scroll the viewport to see the example working</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div style="height: 300px">
        <w-affix class="affix-example" viewport-offset-top="100">
            <button class="btn">I'm affixed!</button>
        </w-affix>
    </div>
</div>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set affixExample1 %}
<w-affix viewport-offset-top="100">
    <button class="btn">I'm affixed!</button>
</w-affix>{% endset %}{{affixExample1|e}}
</pre>

